org.apache.river.test.share

Class AttributesUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.test.share.AttributesUtil

  • public class AttributesUtil
extends Object
    This class contains a set of static methods that provide general-purpose functions for processing sets of attributes; functions such as displaying information about the contents of one or more attribute sets, comparing the contents of two such sets, etc.

      • displayAttributeSet

        public static void displayAttributeSet(net.jini.core.entry.Entry[] attributes,
                                       String attributeSetName,
                                       Level level)
        Using an instance of org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestUtil, displays the contents of the input array whose elements are instances of net.jini.core.entry.Entry. The contents of that array will be displayed only if the QATestUtil instance is configured to display debugging output (qautil.debug=true).
        Parameters:
        attributes - Entry array whose elements correspond to the instances that are to be displayed
        attributeSetName - identifying String that will be displayed along with the contents of the array. This parameter can contain any value, even null, but will typically be set to the name of the array whose contents will be displayed. If null is input, the default String "Attribute Set" will be used.
        level - the logging level

      • displayAttribute

        public static void displayAttribute(net.jini.core.entry.Entry attribute,
                                    String label,
                                    Level level)
        Using an instance of org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestUtil, displays the contents of the attribute parameter. If the attribute parameter is a well-known Entry type, then all of its field values will be displayed; otherwise, only the parameter's string value will be displayed. Note that information about the attribute parameter will be displayed only if the QATestUtil instance is configured to display debugging output (qautil.debug=true).
        Parameters:
        attribute - instance of Entry whose fields string value will be displayed
        level - the logging level

      • compareAttributeSets

        public static boolean compareAttributeSets(net.jini.core.entry.Entry[] attributeSet1,
                                           net.jini.core.entry.Entry[] attributeSet2,
                                           Level level)
        Compares the contents of two sets of attributes ignoring duplicate attributes. If debugging is turned on (qautil.debug=true), this method uses an instance of org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestUtil to display information about the two sets being compared. This method should be invoked by tests that need to compare two sets of attributes for equivalent content in which duplicate attributes are unimportant.
        Parameters:
        attributeSet1 - Entry array containing the first set of attribute instances that are to be compared
        attributeSet2 - Entry array containing the second set of attribute instances that are to be compared
        level - the logging level
        Returns:
        true if the sets are equivalent.
